This is how a webpage appears on screen.

How Browser Builds CSSOM
When browser reads CSS:
                                      body {
                                        background-color: blue;
                                      }
                                      
                                      p {
                                        color: red;
                                      }

It parses it and builds a tree-like structure internally. Something like this conceptually:

